Project: Investigate a Dataset
Medical Appointment No Shows

This is a dataset from Kaggle that collects information from 110,527 medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment which contains 14 variables/characteristics. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row. The aim of this analyzes is to detect which of the variables affects the show up of a patient.

  • ScheduledDay tells us on what day the patient set up their appointment.
  • Neighborhood indicates the location of the hospital.
  • Scholarship indicates whether or not the patient is enrolled in Brasilian welfare program Bolsa Famlia.
  • Be careful about the encoding of the last column: it says No if the patient showed up to their appointment, and Yes if they did not show up.
  • PatientId: A number that uniquely identifies a patients (Primary Key)

Here in this notebook is on the analysis of patients showing up for their Medical Appointment with asking the following questions.

  • Can patient age affect their show-up?
  • What is the ratio of gender showing up for an appointment?
  • Do we have more female patient than the male?
  • Does a particular disease affect the show-up of patients?
  • Does a kind of disease affect the show-up of patients?
  • What month had the most appointment?
  • Does month affect the show up of patients?
  • Does sms alert affect the showup of patients for an appointment?
  • Does scholarsihp affect the show up of patients?
  • Does location of patients affect their show up?

Observations¶

  • No word such as Handcap. Renaming of column (Handicap)
  • Age has a wrong record (No one can be -1 years old)
  • No duplicate records
  • Median Ahe is 37.0
  • The dataset contain no missing |value
  • ScheduledDay and AppointmentDay have incorrect datatype (object instead of datetime)
  • The dataset contains 14 metadata/columns
  • The dataset has 110527 records

  • PatientId and AppointmentID has an incorrect datatype (float instead of object) but float is used to manage space

    Where 0 = False and 1 = True in column Scholarship, Hipertension, Diabetes, Alcoholism, and SMS_received.

    Where 0 = Not handcap, 1 = fairly-handcap_1, 2 = fairly-handcap_2, 3 = handcap, 4 = highly handcap in column Handcap

# Cutting continuous variables (Age) into segments.

bin_edges = [0, 20, 40, 60, 80, 100, 120]
bin_names = ['Child/Teenager', 'Young Adult', 'Adult', 'Elder', 'More Elderly', 'Aged']
df['age_category'] = pd.cut(df['Age'], bin_edges, labels = bin_names)

df_age = df[['Age','No-show', 'age_category']].groupby(['age_category', 'No-show']).count().sort_values(by='Age', ascending= False).unstack()

we can see that 32% of patients got at least an sms but only 23% showed up compared to 68% of patients not getting an sms but only 57% were around; so sms does not affect the the show up of patient

Conclusion - Communication

1. Patient Age has a relationship on the show up of patient.

2. More Females showed up for their appointment i.e they seems to be more concious of their health

3. SMS alert has no impact to the show up of patients

4. Appointment Date affects the show up of patients

5. Diease does not affect the show up of patients

6. being handicapped affects the show up of patients

7. Scolarship has no impact of the show up of patient

Resources: towardsdatascience.com, pandas.pydata.org and Kaggle.com

Limitations

  1. Some other factors e.g weather, transportation etc could be the cause as to why some patients could not meetup for the appointment day

  2. Distance of Patient's location to the Hospital is also a limitation since the dataset didnt contain distance(metre) of a location to the clinic
